ive (I-deck), and Complex (K-deck), and the rulebook encourages players to experiment with the various decks and mixtures thereof. Aftermarket decks such as the Z-Deck and the L-Deck also exist.<br/><br/>Agricola is a turn-based game. There are 14 game rounds occurring in 6 stages, with a Harvest at the end of each stage (after Rounds 4, 7, 9, 11, 13, and 14).<br/>Each player starts with two playing tokens (farmer and spouse) and thus can take two turns, or actions, per round. There are multiple options, and while the game progresses, you'll have more and more: first thing in a round, a new action card is flipped over.<br/>Problem: Each action can be taken by only one player each round, so it's important to do some things with high preference.<br/>Each player also starts with a hand of 7 Occupation cards (of more than 160 total) and 7 Minor Improvement cards (of more than 140 total) that he/she may use during the game if they fit in his/her strategy. Speaking of which, there are countless strategies, some depending on your card hand. Sometimes it's a good choice to stay on course, and sometimes it is better to react to your opponents' actions...<br/><br/>"]} {:tag :thumbnail, :attrs nil, :content ["https://cf.geekdo-images.com/dDDo2Hexl80ucK1IlqTk-g__thumb/img/GHGdnCfeysoP_34gLnofJcNivW8=/fit-in/200x150/filters:strip_icc()/pic831744.jpg"]} {:tag :image, :attrs nil, :content ["https://cf.geekdo-images.com/dDDo2Hexl80ucK1IlqTk-g__original/img/toobKoejPiHpfpHk4SYd1UAJafw=/0x0/filters:format(jpeg)/pic831744.jpg"]} {:tag :boardgamepublisher, :attrs {:objectid "234"}, :content ["Lookout Games"]} {:tag :boardgamepodcastepisode, :attrs {:objectid "238869"}, :content ["#12: More Isn't Always Better"]} {:tag :boardgamepodcastepisode, :attrs {:objectid "106625"}, :content ["#47: AtG Playtest, Agricola &amp; More"]} {:tag :boardgamepodcastepisode, :attrs {:objectid "202958"}, :content ["1P 004 - Luna"]} {:tag :boardgamepodcastepisode, :attrs {:objectid "175520"}, :content ["1P 