 the challenges ahead and emerge victorious?<br/><br/><br/>Game Summary<br/>Each player has their own board, with space for factories, and 3 rail tracks (to 3 different cities). On each track, use a track token to mark the progression of your rails (different colored marker for each type or rail). Some interesting twists:<br/>- The different track types must be built in a specific order (black, gray, brown, natural, white). Later tracks may never be advanced further on the track than the earlier tracks.<br/>- On each track, as the track head advances, you cross several thresholds that provide awards: the ability to start a new color of track, victory points, bonus tiles, etc.<br/>- Each track line can have one (two for the first rail) engine(s) associated with it; the size of the loco(s) determines how far down the track you actually score VP.<br/><br/>The central board has (almost) all the locations for placing workers. Each location requires 1-3 workers (of one player; played all together). Players, who start the game with 5 workers (or 6 workers, in 2-3 player games), will take turns using a location. These provide a variety of abilities, for example:<br/>- advance 1 or more track heads by 1-3 spaces<br/>- acquire an engine or factory; engines are allocated to rail lines, while factories (the reverse side of the tile) are placed on your factory line.<br/>- earn 2 coins<br/>- take 2 temporary workers<br/>- jump ahead in turn order<br/>- acquire an engineer, which has a unique power and becomes a worker-placement location only for you<br/><br/>Each round ends when all players have passed on placing/using workers. Then, score VP for each track and factory line. On each track line, only spaces as far down the track as the loco level will score. Each track type scores VP for every space from its track head back to where the next color of track starts. Track types built earlier (e.g. black) score less/space than later tracks (e.g., white). On each factory line the position of the purple industry marker(s) show how many VP are scored.<br/><br/>After 7 rounds (or 6 rounds, in 2-3 player games), the game ends; most VP wins!<br/><br/>"]} {:tag :thumbnail, :attrs nil, :content ["https://cf.geekdo-images.com/B0oEVgeqs4_rT8oyb1_Juw__thumb/img/oZkHYUMtcGVwg_gz6OjtuiD3vmU=/fit-in/200x150/filters:strip_icc()/pic1772936.jpg"]} {:tag :image, :attrs nil, :content ["https://cf.geekdo-images.com/B0oEVgeqs4_rT8oyb1_Juw__original/img/EnBmUkDKSbcBusI6nVRczadYs0M=/0x0/filters:format(jpeg)/pic1772936.jpg"]} {:tag :boardgamepublisher, :attrs {:objectid "133"}, :content ["Hans im Glück"]} {:tag :boardgamehonor, :attrs {:objectid "61145"}, :content ["2013 Board Game Quest Awards Best Strategy/Euro Game Nominee"]} {:tag :boardgamehonor, :attrs {:objectid "65433"}, :content ["2013 Jocul Anului în România Advanced Finalist"]} {:tag :boardgamehonor, :attrs {:objectid "25317"}, :content ["2013 Meeples' Choice Nominee"]} {:tag :boardgamehonor, :attrs {:objectid "27657"}, :content ["2013 Meeples' Choice Winner"]} {:tag :boardgamehonor, :attrs {:objectid "25830"}, :content ["2014 Deutscher Spiele Preis Best Family/Adult Game Winner"]} {:tag :boardgamehonor, :attrs {:objectid "27156"}, :content ["2014 Gouden Ludo Nominee"]} {:tag :boardgamehonor, :attrs {:objectid "25787"}, :content ["2014 International Gamers Award - General Strategy: Multi-player Nominee"]} {:tag :boardgamehonor, :attrs {:objectid "26200"}, :content ["2014 International Gamers Award - General Strategy: Multi-player Winner"]} {:tag :boardgamehonor, :attrs {:objectid "32977"}, :content ["2014 Jogo do Ano Nominee"]} {:tag :boardgamehonor, :attrs {:objectid "65473"}, :content ["2014 JUG Adult Game of the Year Finalist"]} {:tag :boardgamehonor, :attrs {:objectid "25147"}, :content ["2014 Kennerspiel des Jahres Recommended"]} {:tag :boardgamehonor, :attrs {:objectid "35455"}, :content ["2014 Lys Passioné Finalist"]} {:tag :boardgamehonor, :attrs {:objectid "35452"}, :content ["2014 Lys Passioné Win